MID-60-tools — self-hosted scoring engine for the Multidimensional Inventory
of Dissociation, 60-item version.

Software in this repository: MIT licence (see below).

Instrument content (item wording, subscale assignments, clinical cut-offs,
16-category profile classification rules, percentile tables and interpretive
text) is reproduced from:

  Kate, M.-A. & Hegarty, D. L. (2026). A Review of the Clinical Utility and
  Psychometric Properties of the Multidimensional Inventory of Dissociation
  – 60-item Version (MID-60): Norms, Percentile Rankings, and Qualitative
  Descriptors. https://doi.org/10.17605/OSF.IO/E83KC

That technical paper carries an open-source licence (p. 2): "The information
in this document can be used without permission by researchers and clinicians
and distributed under an open source licence." The MID-60 itself was
developed by Kate, M.-A., Jamieson, G., Dorahy, M. J., & Middleton, W.
(2021), J Trauma & Dissociation 22(3): 265-287
(https://doi.org/10.1080/15299732.2020.1792024), as a short version of the
218-item MID (Dell, 2006).

This is a screening instrument only. It is not designed to be the sole
basis for diagnosis and should always be interpreted alongside clinical
judgment by a qualified clinician.

